               <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1807">Internally dated to the year <foreign xml:lang="ta">aṭceya</foreign> of the Jovian cycle, that is, CE 1806-1807, 1746-1747, etc. See colophon (U3, f66v5). Dated to circa 1820 by Vinson (1868) and to 1780 by Cabaton (1912), on unstated grounds (presumably palaeographical and material analysis arguments). Not after 1854, since part of the collection of <persName role="collector">Édouard Ariel</persName> (1818-1854), bequested in 1855 to the Société Asiatique, Paris (Rosny 1868).</origDate>
                     <origPlace>Tamilnadu.</origPlace>
                  </origin><provenance><p>Owned by <persName role="collector">Édouard Ariel</persName> (1818-1854). Bequested by Édouard Ariel to Société Asiatique (Rosny 1868, p. 177).</p></provenance><acquisition>
                     <p>Received, August 1st, 1866, from the Société Asiatique. See BnF, département des Manuscrits, inventaire 7 = <title>Dons: manuscrits et imprimés documentaires, 1848-1895</title>, no. 1192.</p>
                     
